In [[geometry]], the '''great deltoidal hexecontahedron''' is a nonconvex [[Isohedral figure|isohedral]] [[polyhedron]]. It is the [[Dual polyhedron|dual]] of the [[nonconvex great rhombicosidodecahedron]]. It is visually identical to the [[Great rhombidodecacron]]. It has 60 intersecting [[cross quadrilateral]] faces, 120 edges, and 62 vertices.

It is also called a ''great strombic hexecontahedron.''

